  "remarks" : " The sum of angles ` m A B C + m B C A + m C A B ` in a triangle adds up to either ` _pi ` or ` -u _pi ` , i.e. 180 degrees.  (The sign is due to the two possible orientations of vertex arrangement and our signed notion of angle).  This is Metamath 100 proof #27.  (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 23-Sep-2014.) ",
